    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "hey my ac unit outside is doing something weird. the fan is making this loud humming sound but the blades arent actually spinning. what could be causing that and is it safe to go out there and look at it?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "That humming noise without movement is a classic sign of a motor issue, often caused by a seized capacitor, a failing motor, or a jammed blade. It is **not safe** to go out there and touch the unit if it is still plugged in, as the capacitor can hold a dangerous charge for a long time, and the blades could suddenly spin if the protection fails. You should unplug the unit immediately and call a professional HVAC technician to diagnose the electrical component.\n\nIf you need to check the breaker box, you can do that from inside your home, but never attempt to open the outdoor casing or touch any wires while the system is powered on. This is a mechanical and electrical emergency that requires specialized tools, and ignoring it could lead to a fire or further damage to your system.",
