    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "that makes sense. it's just frustrating cause it started so suddenly. there was no warning, it was working fine one minute and then just started this weird humming sound. kind of feels like something just randomly broke for no reason. is it normal for these things to just fail out of nowhere like that?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "It is incredibly frustrating when something works perfectly and then suddenly stops, especially when it feels like a random event. While HVAC units are built to last, they are subject to wear and tear, and sudden failures are unfortunately common enough that they happen to most homeowners eventually.\n\nThe \"sudden\" nature of your issue is actually quite typical for capacitor failures, which often occur without any prior warning signs like unusual vibrations or smells. These components can degrade internally over time and then snap catastrophically the moment they are called upon to do their job.\n\nI hope your technician can get this fixed soon so you can get back to enjoying your cool air without worrying about the noise.",
